Cook @penne pasta{8%oz} according to package directions.  Meanwhile, combine @spaghetti sauce{2.5%cups}, @sliced pepperoni{8%oz}, @sliced mushrooms{4.5%oz} (drained from jar), @chopped green pepper{1/2%cup}, @chopped onion{1/2%cup}, @grated Parmesan cheese{1/2%cup}, @garlic powder{1/2%tsp}, @salt{1/2%tsp}, @pepper{1/8%tsp} and @crushed red pepper flakes{1/8%tsp} in a bowl. Drain pasta; add to sauce mixture and mix well.
Transfer to a greased 3-qt. baking dish.  Combine @tomato sauce{8%oz} and @spaghetti sauce{1%cup}; pour over top.
Cover and bake at 350 degrees for 40-~{45%minutes} or until bubbly.  Sprinkle with @mozzarella cheese{2%cups}.  Bake, uncovered, 5-10 minutes longer or until cheese is melted.  Let stand 5 minutes before serving.